####Local Storage
1. Local storage is a storage specific to browser url that is hit by a domain. So every website has its own local storage. 
2. Local storage is limited to 5MB (per domain). 
3. Local storage is persistent, does not get deleted on refresh or closing of browser or any other actions
4. Add, set, get, remove, clear - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/localStorage
5. Why would you use local storage?
Persistent Data Storage, Client-Side Caching, Offline Support, Improved User Experience, Reduced Server Load, Cross-Browser Compatibility
6. Local storage is browser specific.




